### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Direct Debit Sandbox — HTTP Request Collection
### Works with: IntelliJ HTTP Client  |  VS Code REST Client extension
###
### SCENARIO CHEAT SHEET (last 3 digits of debitAccount drive the outcome):
###   001  →  Success
###   101  →  Insufficient funds
###   104  →  Duplicate transaction
###   004  →  Pre-approval pending
###   131  →  Timeout
###   111  →  Inconclusive
###   100  →  General failure
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Shared variables — change these once to affect every request below
@baseUrl      = http://localhost:8080
@transflowId  = TF-SANDBOX-001
@apiKey       = KEY-SANDBOX-ABC
@country      = GH
@merchantId   = MERCH_12345
@productId    = PROD_67890
@callbackUrl  = https://webhook.site/your-unique-id


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. PROVISION
###    Register the callback URL for a merchant + product.
###    Do this FIRST — all subsequent callbacks are sent to this URL.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1a. Register callback (happy path)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}",
  "retryAttempts": 3,
  "skipFactor": 1,
  "daysToDebitDayNotice": "1,3"
}

###

### 1b. Update callback URL (call again with a different URL — overwrites the old one)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "https://webhook.site/updated-url"
}

###

### 1c. Missing credentials — expect responseCode 107
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId:
x-key:

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. SUBSCRIBE
###    Creates a recurring subscription.
###    Returns 03 immediately. Preapproval callback fires after 2s,
###    transaction callback fires after 7s — to the provisioned URL.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2a. Monthly mobile money — success scenario (account ends 001)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_001",
  "debitNotificationAccount": "0241234001",
  "triggerDebitStatus": true,
  "notificationStatus": true,
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "3" },
    { "name": "skipFactor", "value": "1" }
  ]
}

###

### 2b. Weekly debit with end date
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "25.00",
  "frequencyType": "WEEKLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "endDate": "2027-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "09:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_002"
}

###

### 2c. Insufficient funds scenario (account ends 101)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234101",
  "debitAmount": "200.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "1",
  "debitTime": "14:00",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_003"
}

###

### 2d. Duplicate reference — expect responseCode 104
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "referenceNo": "REF_2026_001"
}

###

### 2e. Missing required field (no debitAccount) — expect 400 validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/subscribe
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAmount": "50.00",
  "frequencyType": "MONTHLY",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01",
  "debitDay": "15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. UPDATE SUBSCRIPTION
###    Only send fields you want to change. subscriptionId is always required.
###    Replace SUB_REPLACE_ME with an ID returned from a subscribe call.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3a. Change amount and debit day
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/update
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAmount": "75.00",
  "debitDay": "20",
  "configuration": [
    { "name": "retryAttempts", "value": "4" },
    { "name": "skipFactor", "value": "1" },
    { "name": "daysToDebitDayNotice", "value": "2,5" }
  ]
}

###

### 3b. Subscription not found — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/update
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUBNOTEXIST000",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "debitAmount": "75.00"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 4. CANCEL SUBSCRIPTION
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 4a. Cancel — happy path
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 4b. Cancel — not found
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUBNOTEXIST000",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 5. GET CUSTOMER SUBSCRIPTIONS
###    Returns all subscriptions for a debitAccount on a given product.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5a. Fetch all subscriptions for account
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/customer-subscriptions
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 5b. Account with no subscriptions — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/customer-subscriptions
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "debitAccount": "0000000000",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 6. PAUSE SUBSCRIPTION
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 6a. Pause — happy path
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/pause
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 6b. Pause an already-paused subscription — expect error
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/pause
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 7. RESUME SUBSCRIPTION
###    Only works if the subscription is currently PAUSED.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 7a. Resume — happy path
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/resume-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 7b. Resume a subscription that is not paused — expect error
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/resume-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "subscriptionId": "SUB_REPLACE_ME",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 8. TRIGGER DEBIT
###    Manually triggers a debit for a failed subscription.
###    Uses referenceNo (not subscriptionId) to look up the record.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 8a. Trigger — happy path (will fire transaction callback asynchronously)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/trigger-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_2026_001",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 8b. Trigger — reference not found
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/trigger-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_DOES_NOT_EXIST",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 9. SCHEDULE ONE-TIME DEBIT
###    Schedules a single future debit. debitDate must be 24+ hours away.
###    callbackUrl here is a per-request fallback (provision URL takes priority).
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 9a. Schedule — happy path (success scenario, account ends 001)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/schedule-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "country": "{{country}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "150.00",
  "debitDate": "2026-06-15",
  "debitTime": "14:30",
  "debitNotificationAccount": "0241234001",
  "referenceNo": "REF_SCHED_001",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}"
}

###

### 9b. Schedule — debitDate is today (less than 24h away) — expect responseCode 100
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/schedule-debit
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "merchantId": "{{merchantId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "country": "{{country}}",
  "debitAccount": "0241234001",
  "debitAmount": "150.00",
  "debitDate": "2026-05-07",
  "debitTime": "10:00",
  "referenceNo": "REF_SCHED_002",
  "channel": "MTN",
  "currency": "GHS",
  "callbackUrl": "{{callbackUrl}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 10. RETRIEVE SUBSCRIPTION BY REFERENCE
###     Fetches the full subscription record using the third-party referenceNo.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 10a. Retrieve — happy path
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/retrieve/details/thirdpartyreferenceno
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_2026_001",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

###

### 10b. Retrieve — not found
POST {{baseUrl}}/subscription/retrieve/details/thirdpartyreferenceno
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "referenceId": "REF_DOES_NOT_EXIST",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}


### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 11. CHECK TRANSACTION STATUS
###     Looks up the outcome of a debit using its reference, productId, mandateId.
###     mandateId is returned in the transaction callback payload.
### ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 11a. Check status — found (run after a subscribe + wait 7s for callback)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transaction/check-status
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "reference": "REF_2026_001",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "mandateId": "MAND_REPLACE_ME"
}

###

### 11b. Check status — not found (returns responseCode 99)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transaction/check-status
Content-Type: application/json
x-transflowId: {{transflowId}}
x-key: {{apiKey}}
x-country: {{country}}

{
  "reference": "REF_DOES_NOT_EXIST",
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "mandateId": "MANDNOTEXIST"
}
